</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindner" box="[564,847,1426,1451]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" refString="Lindner, A. &amp; Migotto, A. E. (2002) The life cycle of Clytia linearis and Clytia noliformis: metagenic campanulariids (Cnidaria: Hydrozoa) with contrasting polyp and medusa stages. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 82 (4), 541 - 553. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0025315402005866" type="journal article" year="2002">
Lindner &amp; Migotto 
<number box="[786,847,1426,1450]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,307,1461,1486]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Hydroid.</emphasis>
Hydrorhiza as creeping stolons; colonies stolonal; pedicel strongly annulated basally and distally; hydranth with about 
<number box="[387,457,1498,1523]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="27.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="25.0">25–30</number>
filiform tentacles; hydrothecae campanulate, thick diaphragm, basal chamber shallow, subspherical, margin with about 
<number box="[517,587,1533,1558]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15</number>
blunt, broadly triangular teeth. Colours: hydranth and coenosarc yellowish. Gonothecae laterally flattened, arising from hydrorhiza, on short annulated stalks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,357,1605,1630]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
Habitat 
<typeStatus box="[299,352,1605,1630]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[364,477,1605,1630]" class="Liliopsida" family="Posidoniaceae" genus="Posidonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[364,477,1605,1630]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Posidonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[494,645,1605,1630]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" refString="Boero, F. (1981 a) Systematics and ecology of the hydroid population of two Posidonia oceanica meadows. Pubblicazioni della Stazione zoologica di Napoli, 2 (3), 181 - 197. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1981. tb 00093. x" type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="a">
Boero 
<number box="[572,632,1605,1630]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="1981.0">1981</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[650,666,1605,1630]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" refString="Boero, F. (1981 b) Bathimetric distribution of the epifauna of a Posidonia meadow of the Isle of Ischia (Naples): Hydroids. Rapports et Proces-Verbaux des Reunions Commision Internationale pour l'Exploration Scientifique de la Mer Mediterranee, Monaco, 27 (2), 197 - 198." type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
); on eupelagic 
<taxonomicName box="[837,958,1606,1629]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Sargassaceae" genus="Sargassum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fucales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Heterokontophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,958,1606,1629]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Sargassum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the open North Atlantic Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Calder" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" refString="Calder, D. R. (1991) Shallow-water hydroids of Bermuda. The Thecatae, exclusive of Plumularioidea. Royal Ontario Museum Life Sciences Contribution, 154, i - iv, 1 - 140. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 1352274" type="journal article" year="1991">
Calder 
<number box="[151,211,1642,1666]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" box="[199,1026,1677,1702]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1677,1702]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Substrate.</emphasis>
Algae, 
<taxonomicName box="[409,523,1677,1702]" class="Liliopsida" family="Posidoniaceae" genus="Posidonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[409,523,1677,1702]" italics="true" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Posidonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaves and rhizomes, mussels, and hydroids.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,301,1714,1739]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Medusa.</emphasis>
Adult. Umbrella flatter than a hemisphere, 
<quantity box="[822,891,1714,1739]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
wide, 
<quantity box="[975,1045,1714,1738]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
high; manubrium tubular; mouth quadrate, with 
<number box="[323,337,1750,1774]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
simple lips; 
<number box="[488,502,1750,1774]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
radial canals; gonads elongated, on the distal third or fourth of the radial canals, female gonads bearing 
<number box="[411,481,1786,1811]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20–35</number>
large ova; 
<number box="[606,634,1786,1811]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="16.0">16</number>
marginal tentacles; 
<number box="[859,887,1786,1811]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="16.0">16</number>
intervening statocysts. Colours: bell transparent; gonads, manubrium, bulbs and tentacles assuming the colour of food.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
Developmental stages. Newly released medusa with hemispherical umbrella; manubrium 0.4 height of umbrella; mouth quadrate, with 
<number box="[526,540,1894,1918]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
smooth lips; 
<number box="[703,717,1894,1918]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
perradial canals and one circular canal; velum broad; gonads absent; 
<number box="[238,252,1930,1954]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
perradial marginal tentacular bulbs and 
<number box="[713,727,1930,1954]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number box="[767,781,1930,1954]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
interradial secondary atentacular bulbs usually present; 
<number box="[1422,1436,1930,1954]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="4.0">4</number>
hollow tentacles, with a terminal nematocyst cluster; 
<number box="[748,762,1966,1990]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147" value="8.0">8</number>
adradial statocysts, each with one statolith.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="146.[151,1437,1354,2027]" lastBlockId="147.[151,1436,151,861]" lastPageId="147" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,2002,2027]" pageId="146" pageNumber="147">Cnidome.</emphasis>
A-type microbasic mastigophores and merotrichous isorhizas (polyp); A-, C-, and D-type microbasic mastigophores and holotrichous isorhizas (medusa) (nematocyst nomenclature follows that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ostman" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Ostman, C. (1979 a) Two types of nematocysts in Campanulariidae (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa) studied by light and scanning electron microscopy. Zoologica Scripta, 8 (1 - 4), 5 - 12. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1979. tb 00614. x" type="journal article" year="1979" yearSuffix="a">
Östman, 
<number box="[151,212,188,213]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="1979.0">1979</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ostman" box="[229,244,188,213]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Ostman, C. (1979 b) Nematocysts in the Phialidium medusae of Clytia hemisphaerica (Hydrozoa, Campanulariidae) studied by light and scanning electron microscopy. Zoon, 7 (2), 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="1979" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="147.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,340,223,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">Seasonality.</emphasis>
January (Puce 
<emphasis box="[513,563,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[577,637,224,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), April, August (
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[827,1057,223,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Boero, F. &amp; Fresi, E. (1986) Zonation and evolution of a Rocky bottom hydroid community. Marine Ecology, 7 (2), 123 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1986. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1986">
Boero &amp; Fresi 
<number box="[997,1057,223,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), June (
<bibRefCitation author="Llobet" box="[1144,1376,223,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Llobet Nadal, I. (1987) Faunistica y distribucion espacio-temporal de una poblacion de hydropolipos epibiontes del alga Halimeda tuna en el Mediterraneo occidental. MS Thesis. [pagination unkown]" type="book" year="1987">
Llobet i Nadal 
<number box="[1316,1376,224,248]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="1987.0">1987</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and July (
<bibRefCitation author="Llobet" box="[216,432,260,285]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Llobet, I., Gili, J. M. &amp; Hughes, R. G. (1991) Horizontal, vertical and seasonal distributions of epiphytic Hydrozoa on the alga Halimeda tuna in the northwestern Mediterranean Sea. Marine Biology Berlin, 110 (1), 151 - 159. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / bf 01313102" type="journal article" year="1991">
Llobet 
<emphasis box="[303,357,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[375,432,260,284]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) in the western Mediterranean; October, February (
<bibRefCitation author="Faucci" box="[1040,1300,260,285]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Faucci, A. &amp; Boero, F. (2000) Structure of an epiphytic hydroid community on Cystoseira at two sites of different wave exposure. In: Mills, C. E., Boero, F., Migotto, A. &amp; Gili, J. M. (Eds.), Trends in Hydrozoan Biology - IV. Scientia Marina, 64 (Supplement 1), pp. 255 - 264. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2000.64 s 1255" type="journal article" year="2000">
Faucci &amp; Boero 
<number box="[1242,1300,260,284]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) in Salento waters; January–May, July–December (for a review see Bouillon 
<emphasis box="[885,941,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[948,1009,296,320]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="2004.0">2004</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="147.[151,1436,151,861]" box="[199,1371,332,357]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,452,332,357]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">Reproductive period.</emphasis>
January (Puce 
<emphasis box="[624,673,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="147" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[687,747,332,356]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), and August (
<bibRefCitation author="Boero" box="[909,1135,332,357]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" refString="Boero, F. &amp; Fresi, E. (1986) Zonation and evolution of a Rocky bottom hydroid community. Marine Ecology, 7 (2), 123 - 150. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1439 - 0485.1986. tb 00152. x" type="journal article" year="1986">
Boero &amp; Fresi 
<number box="[1078,1135,332,357]" pageId="147" pageNumber="148" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) in the Ligurian Sea.
</paragraph>
